contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

01:00.600 --> 01:04.036
MAN: <i>Operation Savior launches</i>
<i>in just a few short hours.</i>

01:04.160 --> 01:06.674
<i>Mankind's only hope.</i>

01:06.800 --> 01:11.954
<i>A single rocket hastily assembled</i>
<i>by a multinational team of scientists.</i>

01:13.280 --> 01:15.316
<i>There's no backup plan.</i>

01:15.440 --> 01:18.876
<i>If today's launch fails,</i>
<i>all hope is gone.</i>

02:02.480 --> 02:04.675
(NOISY CROWD)

02:04.800 --> 02:06.756
Oh, excuse me.
You don't recognize this woman?

02:08.080 --> 02:10.958
Hey, do you recognize this woman?
She's got a little girl, about six?

02:11.080 --> 02:12.149
Excuse me...

02:12.280 --> 02:17.274
Hey! Jamie! Get her a monster truck!
Girls love monster trucks, right?

02:17.400 --> 02:19.914
Yeah. I'm actually quite keen
on making a good first impression

02:20.040 --> 02:22.713
on my daughter so probably not.

02:22.840 --> 02:24.512
Oh! I'll get her a giraffe.

02:24.640 --> 02:26.517
Jude said she likes giraffes.

02:26.640 --> 02:28.596
In fact, it's the only thing
he told me about her.

02:28.720 --> 02:31.439
I don't know her name but I know
where she stands giraffe-wise.

02:32.360 --> 02:34.271
Something for Layla, perhaps?

02:34.400 --> 02:36.709
OK, so this is exactly
what I was talking about.

02:36.840 --> 02:39.673
This is gonna be hard enough as it is
without you being a dick to Layla.

02:39.800 --> 02:41.791
What possible justification
could I have for that?

02:41.920 --> 02:44.434
Oh, yeah,
she's slightly married to your brother.

02:44.560 --> 02:46.198
I just want to meet my daughter

02:46.320 --> 02:49.471
and find out the truth
in the most painless way possible, OK?

02:49.600 --> 02:53.878
- Do me a favor and haggle for that?
- (GIRAFFE SQUEAKS)

03:03.320 --> 03:08.394
Congratulations. You have completed
your fast-track Level Six.

03:08.520 --> 03:11.114
You have transcended
the dimension of self

03:11.240 --> 03:15.631
and are finally ready to open yourself
to the love of others.

03:16.760 --> 03:18.591
Now do we get to meet the Messiah?

03:18.720 --> 03:23.475
No, to meet Ruthless
you must all travel to Paradise Island.

03:23.600 --> 03:25.352
Great, so where do I get a ticket?

03:25.480 --> 03:27.118
It's not that simple.

03:28.200 --> 03:30.077
First, you must choose a partner...

03:30.200 --> 03:34.034
- Got one. Got one right here.
- And then you must get married.

03:34.160 --> 03:38.995
Ruthless teaches us
that you cannot reach paradise alone,

03:39.120 --> 03:42.590
so I suggest you choose wisely.
(LAUGHS) Thank you.

03:42.720 --> 03:44.676
There's got to be another way.

03:44.800 --> 03:50.113
Believe me, marriage is the only path
to happiness and salvation.

03:53.440 --> 03:55.908
We are out of here.

03:56.040 --> 03:58.076
Real religions do not have levels.

03:58.200 --> 04:00.350
- Investigation over.
- Hindus have levels.

04:00.480 --> 04:02.914
OK, but they don't hand out badges.

04:03.040 --> 04:06.669
Jude, not one person who's gone
to this island has returned.

04:06.800 --> 04:09.837
We must find those people.
We have to give their families answers.

04:09.960 --> 04:12.155
Come on. Let's get hitched.

04:12.280 --> 04:13.395
OK.

04:17.200 --> 04:18.997
(NOISY CROWD)

04:21.120 --> 04:23.680
Alright, mate? Hey, hey,
are you interested in seeds, yeah?

04:23.800 --> 04:26.792
I've got carrot, tomato, beetroot.
Premium gear.

04:26.920 --> 04:28.638
Actually, I'm looking for a woman?

04:28.760 --> 04:32.958
That's not really my scene, mate.
I can do you water filters, fertilizers.

04:33.080 --> 04:35.435
Trust me. Survive this,
you're gonna need to grow your own.

04:35.560 --> 04:38.632
Don't get me wrong. I hope Saviour
works but it pays to prep, right?

04:39.400 --> 04:43.188
- Yeah, this is her.
- Oh yeah, that's Sophie.

04:43.320 --> 04:45.436
- Sophie?
- Yeah. She did my last MOT.

04:45.560 --> 04:49.838
- She's a great mechanic.
- OK. And where is Sophie?

04:49.960 --> 04:51.518
What's it worth?

04:53.160 --> 04:55.230
No, I don't want your money.
I want your tins.

04:56.800 --> 04:58.358
Alright.

04:59.440 --> 05:01.078
- Sweet corn.
- Yeah.

05:02.560 --> 05:03.959
- OK. Kidney beans.
- Yeah.

05:04.080 --> 05:07.311
Cream of mushroom soup.
And whatever the hell that is.

05:09.720 --> 05:12.996
She's at the courthouse.
She was arrested this morning. Come on.

05:13.120 --> 05:14.951
ARIEL: Got ya!

05:15.080 --> 05:16.911
She's been arrested in Suffolk.

05:17.040 --> 05:21.079
Right. Let's go. You drive.

05:21.200 --> 05:24.909
I'm perfectly capable
of snatching the kid by myself.

05:25.040 --> 05:27.952
Yeah. Grandma doesn't want you
going out on your own.

05:28.080 --> 05:31.629
- Oh. That's very sweet of her.
- Mm. Isn't it?

05:31.760 --> 05:34.354
You know how she worries about you.

05:41.640 --> 05:46.111
This is insane! Rhonda. Please.
Look, you are on the run.

05:46.240 --> 05:48.151
You cannot go to the hospital.

05:48.280 --> 05:51.590
I didn't come all this way
to just sit a few miles from my husband.

05:52.960 --> 05:55.793
- I got to at least try.
- Are you serious?

05:55.920 --> 06:00.436
This could be the last time
we're together ever! Think about it.

06:00.560 --> 06:02.710
Everyone's gonna be watching
your rocket launch.

06:02.840 --> 06:06.150
This could be my best chance,
my only chance.

06:07.840 --> 06:09.831
So unless
you've got some better ideas...

06:14.280 --> 06:17.033
Please, please take care of yourself.
OK?

06:17.160 --> 06:20.755
Cos with Arnie gone,
you're literally all I've got.

06:20.880 --> 06:22.518
(PHONE PINGS)

06:23.320 --> 06:24.878
OK, I've gotta go.

06:33.840 --> 06:36.070
- Where have you been?
- I know. I'm sorry. I had to...

06:36.200 --> 06:38.555
- Arnie, we have to talk.
- Not here!

06:38.680 --> 06:40.671
Please, just listen to me, please.

06:40.800 --> 06:43.792
I love you. I love you and I miss you.

06:43.920 --> 06:47.959
And I can't function without you
and I...

06:48.080 --> 06:50.116
Look, I think it's stupid
that we should throw away

06:50.240 --> 06:51.912
something as good as us just because...

06:52.040 --> 06:54.474
Scotty? Scotty, please.

06:55.680 --> 07:00.310
Now is not the time. You need to
pull yourself together. Now come on.

07:04.280 --> 07:06.032
(CHATTER)

07:07.560 --> 07:09.437
That's alright. That's alright.

07:10.520 --> 07:13.671
Uh... Morning, everybody.

07:14.160 --> 07:16.151
Uh... I apologize for the delay

07:16.280 --> 07:19.716
but as you can imagine
we've been somewhat busy today.

07:19.840 --> 07:23.992
Scotty McNeil, Senior Adviser,
Special Situations Group,

07:24.120 --> 07:28.318
will run briefly through our timetable
and then we'll take any questions.

07:28.440 --> 07:29.953
Scotty.

07:32.280 --> 07:33.269
Um...

07:34.680 --> 07:35.908
Um...

07:37.120 --> 07:41.511
(MONOTONE) The Operation Saviour launch
will take place today at 1700 hours.

07:41.640 --> 07:44.393
Assuming the launch succeeds,
it will take seven days for the craft

07:44.520 --> 07:46.351
to reach the comet.

07:46.480 --> 07:49.756
We're not trying to destroy the comet.
It's too big.

07:49.880 --> 07:53.509
We just want to deflect it enough
so that it safely misses Earth.

07:57.000 --> 07:59.594
- Um...
- Yeah. Think of it like a game of pool.

07:59.720 --> 08:02.154
The Earth is the cue. Uh...

08:02.280 --> 08:05.955
Well, the... the craft is the cue ball

08:06.080 --> 08:08.196
and the comet is the eight ball.

08:11.360 --> 08:13.078
Right.

08:17.400 --> 08:20.233
Saviour contains a nuclear warhead

08:20.360 --> 08:23.272
which we plan
to detonate on the comet's surface.

08:23.400 --> 08:27.871
In order to do this,
the comet will split into t...

08:30.160 --> 08:31.912
(PEOPLE MUTTER QUIETLY)

08:32.039 --> 08:34.634
SCOTTY: I'm sorry, the craft will split.

08:34.760 --> 08:36.318
Excuse me.

08:38.720 --> 08:40.472
- I can't do this.
- (PEOPLE MUTTER)

08:40.600 --> 08:44.878
Uh... Ladies and gentlemen,
once again, my apologies.

08:45.000 --> 08:48.151
(VOICE MUFFLED IN BACKGROUND)

09:03.480 --> 09:08.270
Scotty McNeil.
I have a warrant for your arrest.

09:09.880 --> 09:13.111
Right, so what exactly is the plan?

09:13.240 --> 09:15.231
Because just walking up
to random six-year-olds

09:15.360 --> 09:18.557
and offering them cuddly toys
is how you end up in a place like this.

09:18.680 --> 09:20.318
It's a bit...

09:22.760 --> 09:24.113
Dave, look.

09:25.960 --> 09:30.112
- Do you think...
- DAVE: I don't know, man.

09:30.240 --> 09:32.913
No offense
but she's kind of normal looking.

09:34.880 --> 09:36.359
Oh, God.

09:36.480 --> 09:38.516
Oh, wow.

09:40.120 --> 09:42.190
I actually feel a bit sick.

09:44.200 --> 09:45.838
Maybe it's not her.

09:47.640 --> 09:50.473
Daddy! That's my daddy!

10:08.520 --> 10:10.158
Oh, wow.

10:11.960 --> 10:14.599
This is a very happy moment for me.

10:16.480 --> 10:18.755
It's so great to meet you.

10:18.880 --> 10:22.395
- I'm your dad!
- I know. And that's Dave.

10:22.520 --> 10:23.999
Mum told me all about you.

10:24.120 --> 10:27.829
- I don't actually know your name.
- It's Frankie.

10:27.960 --> 10:30.633
- Pleased to meet you, Frankie.
- What's that?

10:30.760 --> 10:32.671
- It's for you.
- (GIRAFFE SQUEAKS)

10:32.800 --> 10:35.030
I heard you like giraffes and stuff
so...

10:37.040 --> 10:40.874
- Do you like it?
- I'd have preferred a monster truck.

10:41.000 --> 10:42.274
(COUGHS) Told you.

10:43.720 --> 10:46.439
It's all going to be alright,
isn't it, Dad?

10:46.560 --> 10:49.120
Cos you're gonna help Mum
and they'll let her go

10:49.240 --> 10:50.992
and we can all go home
and live together.

10:51.120 --> 10:52.155
Listen...

10:52.280 --> 10:56.592
Daddy, you did come to help Mum, right?
Cos that's what good dads do.

10:58.920 --> 11:02.754
Yeah. Right. That's what good dads do.

11:04.000 --> 11:05.319
FRANKIE: Come on, Dave.

11:05.880 --> 11:06.949
- (GIRAFFE SQUEAKS)
- Ow!

11:07.080 --> 11:08.069
Come on.

11:08.200 --> 11:13.479
Hm. Yeah. No. Maybe lose the wig.

11:13.600 --> 11:15.591
- Really?
- Yeah. Hmm.

11:15.720 --> 11:18.553
- OK.
- Put the black ones in again.

11:18.680 --> 11:21.956
But... Honey, it's gonna be fine.

11:22.080 --> 11:26.198
Really. I learned a lot on the run.
Most people don't really notice stuff.

11:26.320 --> 11:28.197
Besides, I've got you.

11:28.320 --> 11:30.709
You're gonna knock out
the surveillance cameras.

11:30.840 --> 11:31.909
- Right.
- Yeah.

11:32.040 --> 11:35.953
And I just... I don't know, Mom.

11:36.080 --> 11:39.516
It's gonna be OK. I believe in you.

11:41.160 --> 11:44.436
I don't like being made a fool of,
Scotty.

11:44.560 --> 11:46.755
It sticks in my craw.

11:46.880 --> 11:51.112
Your phone records show
the 911 came from you.

11:51.240 --> 11:54.118
That is aiding and abetting
a wanted terrorist.

11:54.240 --> 11:56.515
Tell us where to find her.

11:56.640 --> 12:01.953
Are you insane?
Do you know what I do for a living?

12:02.080 --> 12:04.753
Saviour launches in a couple of hours.

12:04.880 --> 12:06.791
You literally
could not have picked a worse day.

12:06.920 --> 12:10.549
On the contrary. You see,
you need to get out of here and you can

12:10.680 --> 12:13.114
if you give me your sister.

12:13.240 --> 12:15.151
It's called leverage, Scotty.

12:15.280 --> 12:16.713
(SLURPS)

12:16.840 --> 12:19.400
Well, you ain't gonna break me.

12:19.520 --> 12:23.115
- (DOOR SLAMS)
- TV: <i>It must be absolutely exhausting.</i>

12:23.240 --> 12:26.437
<i>So these pictures are coming live now</i>
<i>from Operation Saviour.</i>

12:26.560 --> 12:31.588
- This is life sentence for me.
- Well, I'm looking at two to five.

12:31.720 --> 12:33.836
I know
I'll probably never work in DC again

12:33.960 --> 12:38.158
but, hey, at least I can always say
I helped save the world.

12:38.280 --> 12:41.590
Blame Russian president
for predicament of me.

12:41.720 --> 12:43.711
69 ruble to dollar.

12:43.840 --> 12:47.469
If not for him, I wouldn't come here.

12:47.600 --> 12:49.318
- (BANGS DOOR)
- I wouldn't be criminal.

12:51.480 --> 12:55.268
In my country, we have joke now.

12:55.400 --> 12:59.678
Ladies and gentlemen,
you will soon be land in Moscow.

12:59.800 --> 13:02.439
You do not adjust your watches
for daylight saving.

13:02.560 --> 13:06.917
Just wind them back to 1989. (LAUGHS)

13:10.280 --> 13:13.750
- It's funny, no?
- What did you say?

13:13.880 --> 13:15.472
It's much funnier in mother tongue.

13:15.600 --> 13:19.434
No, no, no, the other bit,
the bit about daylight savings.

13:19.560 --> 13:21.915
- Yes, it's finished.
- Oh, my God.

13:22.040 --> 13:23.234
President get rid of.

13:24.840 --> 13:27.115
TV: <i>The stakes</i>
<i>literally could not be higher...</i>

13:27.240 --> 13:30.152
Guard! Guard!

13:32.320 --> 13:34.550
(PEOPLE SHOUT)

13:37.120 --> 13:39.998
MAN: Did you or didn't you
steal the inhaler?

13:40.120 --> 13:43.795
LAYLA: Your Honor,
my daughter is six and she has asthma.

13:43.920 --> 13:46.480
Now by law her inhaler should be free

13:46.600 --> 13:50.957
but instead
the chemist wanted 80 quid for it.

13:51.080 --> 13:52.752
- (GASPS FROM GALLERY)
- 80 quid!

13:52.880 --> 13:54.950
Now that's the real crime here.

13:55.080 --> 13:56.479
(CHEERING)

13:56.600 --> 13:59.273
- (JUDGE BANGS GAVEL)
- Order! Order!

13:59.400 --> 14:02.392
LAYLA: People shouldn't be making a
quick buck out of the end of the world.

14:02.520 --> 14:03.873
We should be helping each other.

14:04.000 --> 14:08.869
I don't have L80, Your Honor,
so, yes, I took the inhaler.

14:09.000 --> 14:11.275
Why aren't you charging the wankers
at the chemist's?

14:11.400 --> 14:14.870
- (CHEERING)
- JUDGE: Order! Order!

14:15.000 --> 14:18.276
I would remind you
this is a court of law

14:18.400 --> 14:22.154
and would you please not say that word?

14:22.280 --> 14:26.034
I'm sorry, what word, Your Honor?
Chemist?

14:26.160 --> 14:27.798
(LAUGHTER)

14:27.920 --> 14:29.478
Oh! Oh, sorry, wankers?

14:29.600 --> 14:32.717
You don't want me to say wankers?

14:32.840 --> 14:36.799
Sorry.
Let the record reflect my deep regret

14:36.920 --> 14:40.230
at my repeated use of the word
(SHOUTS) wankers!

14:40.360 --> 14:41.759
(CHEERING AND APPLAUSE)

14:42.840 --> 14:44.319
JUDGE: Very amusing, Miss Carlton.

14:45.200 --> 14:47.555
(JUDGE'S VOICE FADES)

14:55.880 --> 14:58.678
I fine you L400.

14:58.800 --> 15:03.999
I said your fine is L400
to be paid immediately.

15:04.920 --> 15:09.948
If I had L400, I would have just
bought the inhaler, Your Honor.

15:11.280 --> 15:14.795
You leave me no choice.
One week in prison.

15:14.920 --> 15:16.558
- (SHOUTING)
- That's ridiculous!

15:16.680 --> 15:17.874
What about my daughter?

15:18.000 --> 15:19.433
- I'll pay.
- (SILENCE)

15:19.560 --> 15:22.028
(CHEERING)

15:26.040 --> 15:27.314
Who's this?

15:28.760 --> 15:30.751
My husband, Your Honor.

15:37.280 --> 15:39.475
She's six years old.
She's gonna scream.

15:39.600 --> 15:42.831
No. A bit of chloroform and a hankie
over the nose, she won't make a sound.

15:42.960 --> 15:45.997
- Trust me, I know what I'm doing.
- Looks like it.

15:46.960 --> 15:49.474
I'm guessing you're single, right?

15:50.760 --> 15:54.833
Most people have a picnic blanket,
maybe a Frisbee.

15:54.960 --> 15:58.077
I'm not most people.
Put it down. I wasn't born yesterday.

16:05.400 --> 16:06.674
You're not getting rid of me.

16:06.800 --> 16:09.951
Your gran doesn't trust you
and neither do I. That's why I'm here.

16:10.080 --> 16:12.514
I'll do the chloroform.
You do the gaffer tape.

16:12.640 --> 16:17.395
Fine. Suit yourself.
So where's the gaffer tape?

16:33.240 --> 16:35.834
We need to get our story straight.
You are Federico.

16:35.960 --> 16:37.632
Terrible with names. Hope I remember it.

16:37.760 --> 16:40.877
- The neurosurgeon.
- Well, thanks for picking that!

16:41.000 --> 16:44.549
With my vast knowledge in the field,
I'm sure I won't be tripped up.

16:44.680 --> 16:46.830
- Who are you?
- I am Luisa.

16:46.960 --> 16:48.313
I live in the hills above Verona

16:48.440 --> 16:50.829
where I run the home of orphanage
and donkeys.

16:50.960 --> 16:52.678
- (YAWNS)
- You don't like donkeys?

16:52.800 --> 16:55.439
They're boring.
And the kid thing freaks me out.

16:55.560 --> 16:58.472
- And I play the guitar.
- So basically I'm marrying a nun.

16:58.600 --> 17:02.832
Hi! Logistical question.
When does the last ferry leave?

17:02.960 --> 17:04.075
9pm.

17:04.200 --> 17:07.431
But don't worry.
You won't need a boat back.

17:07.560 --> 17:09.550
No one leaves paradise.

17:10.880 --> 17:12.438
I'll take your word for it.

17:14.680 --> 17:17.398
- Thank you.
- (PEOPLE SHOUT IN QUEUE)

17:18.960 --> 17:21.190
- I appreciate it.
- Pleasure.

17:22.560 --> 17:26.951
- So you're alive then?
- (LAUGHS) Obviously.

17:27.079 --> 17:28.832
(SQUEAKING)

17:28.960 --> 17:31.349
OK. Stop!

17:31.480 --> 17:33.869
JAMIE: I'm loving the news I'm a dad.

17:34.000 --> 17:36.992
Information that would have been nice
to have had before now.

17:39.440 --> 17:42.159
Hi, I'm here to pay the fine for...

17:42.280 --> 17:44.191
What are you calling yourself
these days?

17:44.320 --> 17:46.788
Sophie Carlton. Thanks.

17:46.920 --> 17:51.152
I'm sorry, OK? But everything I did
I promise I did for a good reason.

17:51.280 --> 17:54.670
Oh, OK. I'll just take your word
for that, then, shall I?

17:54.800 --> 17:57.394
After all, I've no reason
to believe you'd ever lie to me!

17:58.040 --> 18:02.238
Just to be clear, I'm not here for you.

18:02.360 --> 18:06.273
All I want is to know my daughter
and maybe find out the truth.

18:06.400 --> 18:08.994
Excuse me. This card's been declined.

18:09.120 --> 18:12.237
Um... That's all I've got. I...

18:12.360 --> 18:13.634
Got a car?

18:13.760 --> 18:16.797
- I've got a minibus.
- That'll do.

18:19.520 --> 18:21.397
I owe you one.

18:22.440 --> 18:23.793
One.

18:25.200 --> 18:27.794
WOMAN: You may kiss the bride.

18:33.120 --> 18:34.917
I forgot about the kiss.

18:35.840 --> 18:38.479
We'll just do it very professionally
and close our eyes.

18:43.800 --> 18:46.360
(# BRIDAL MARCH)

18:46.480 --> 18:49.074
Ah, so that's where the new messiah
must be hanging out.

18:51.880 --> 18:54.269
You need to look convincing.
You are in love with me, right?

18:54.400 --> 18:56.152
Why wouldn't I be?

18:57.800 --> 18:59.916
(MUSIC STOPS SUDDENLY)

19:00.040 --> 19:02.600
Are there any reasons
why you should not be lawfully married?

19:02.720 --> 19:06.395
- Absolutely none.
- Then place your hand upon the Bible.

19:14.600 --> 19:16.192
Federico...

19:16.320 --> 19:18.038
Federico.

19:19.560 --> 19:21.039
Oh, yes.

19:21.160 --> 19:23.355
Will you take Luisa to be your wife?

19:23.480 --> 19:24.754
Will you love her, honor her,

19:24.880 --> 19:27.235
comfort and protect her,
and forsaking all others

19:27.360 --> 19:29.715
be faithful to her
as long as you both shall live?

19:29.840 --> 19:30.875
I will.

19:32.080 --> 19:35.277
Luisa, will you take Federico
to be your husband?

19:35.400 --> 19:36.753
Yes, I will.

19:39.080 --> 19:41.230
Then place the ring upon her finger.

19:45.480 --> 19:49.155
I now declare you man and wife.
You may kiss the bride.

20:09.840 --> 20:11.319
(APPLAUSE)

20:19.520 --> 20:21.431
(CLEARS THROAT)

20:28.840 --> 20:33.675
I have to get a message to
General Gaines or we're all screwed.

20:33.800 --> 20:35.870
Don't tell me.
Only you can save mankind?

20:36.000 --> 20:37.797
SCOTTY: This isn't a joke, OK?

20:37.920 --> 20:41.356
I think there might be
a slight flaw in a piece of code

20:41.480 --> 20:45.189
that the Russians wrote and I don't know
if anyone has noticed it yet.

20:45.320 --> 20:46.639
You want out, give me your sister.

20:46.760 --> 20:50.833
No, that... That... That is not fair!

20:50.960 --> 20:52.552
TESS: OK. Your choice.

20:52.680 --> 20:55.319
Just please can you get General Gaines
on the phone

20:55.440 --> 20:58.876
or anyone else from Mission Control?

20:59.000 --> 21:01.195
What don't you understand?

21:02.360 --> 21:05.716
If Saviour fails we're dead!
We're all dead!

21:05.840 --> 21:07.512
Including your sister
so if you love her,

21:07.640 --> 21:09.710
if you wanna save her life,
tell me where she is.

21:09.840 --> 21:12.957
We're talking about
the entire human race here.

21:13.080 --> 21:15.548
- Are you out of your fucking mind?
- No, and neither are you.

21:15.680 --> 21:16.874
And you're a good man

21:17.000 --> 21:20.037
and you're not going to risk
the entire world for your sister.

21:20.160 --> 21:22.071
So where is she?

21:23.560 --> 21:25.118
Where is she, Scotty?

21:26.120 --> 21:29.317
You need to tell her.
I need to save my <i>mamushka.</i>

21:29.440 --> 21:32.159
- (SOBS)
- Come on.

21:33.880 --> 21:35.598
Come on, just tell me.

21:38.520 --> 21:41.990
Keep walking.
It's the next room on the left.

21:42.120 --> 21:43.553
There are no guards on the door.

21:43.680 --> 21:46.717
I'm gonna shut off their surveillance
now, Mom. Good luck.

21:49.200 --> 21:51.589
- SPIKE: <i>It's done.</i>
- OK.

21:53.000 --> 21:54.433
I'm going in.

22:10.720 --> 22:12.358
Rajesh?

22:16.360 --> 22:17.509
(SIGHS)

22:28.520 --> 22:30.636
(SCREAMS)

22:30.760 --> 22:34.230
Please! Please!
No, you don't understand!

22:35.680 --> 22:38.797
I'm sorry! I love you!
I'm sorry! I'm sorry!

22:48.120 --> 22:49.314
(SIGHS)

22:50.640 --> 22:53.473
Well, I think that we fooled them.

22:53.600 --> 22:55.397
Absolutely. You were very convincing.

22:55.520 --> 22:58.318
Thank you.
Well, Freddie is a very passionate man.

22:58.440 --> 23:02.513
There you are! Oh, look at you two!

23:02.640 --> 23:04.710
- Congratulations.
- Thank you.

23:04.840 --> 23:06.990
Such a lovely couple.

23:07.120 --> 23:09.315
Come, sit, sit.

23:11.920 --> 23:16.072
I'm Arless and this is my wife Ruth.

23:16.200 --> 23:17.519
They call us Ruthless.

23:17.640 --> 23:21.076
You know, like Brangelina?

23:21.200 --> 23:23.316
Let's have a drink, celebrate.

23:24.480 --> 23:30.430
So, they say you have been
appointed by God. That must be... nice.

23:30.560 --> 23:34.997
Sure is. He spoke to me.

23:35.120 --> 23:38.590
He told me
to recreate the Garden of Eden.

23:38.720 --> 23:41.314
You win 300 million on the lottery,
I mean,

23:41.440 --> 23:44.273
you know God's
trying to tell you something, right?

23:44.400 --> 23:46.516
Listen, can people leave here?

23:46.640 --> 23:48.676
(BOTH LAUGH)

23:49.880 --> 23:52.633
Why would you want to leave paradise?

23:53.320 --> 23:55.356
We teach love here.

23:55.480 --> 23:58.392
Love without guilt.

23:58.520 --> 24:01.512
None of that BS churches teach.

24:01.640 --> 24:03.710
Real love.

24:04.640 --> 24:08.394
Look at these two.
Such a beautiful couple.

24:14.840 --> 24:17.354
Well, this is it.
We've been living the dream.

24:17.480 --> 24:21.678
I'm going to show Dad my bedroom
and my sunflowers and my castle.

24:21.800 --> 24:23.313
Wow!

24:23.440 --> 24:26.432
You built all of this yourself?
Seriously?

24:26.560 --> 24:30.394
I've been holding him together for the
last seven years. It's not been easy.

24:31.800 --> 24:35.588
Honestly, you have no idea
how much you hurt him.

24:35.720 --> 24:39.872
So if there's a shred of decency in you,
don't fuck him around again, OK?

24:41.480 --> 24:43.630
Frankie? Frankie?

24:43.760 --> 24:46.069
Me and Daddy need to talk.

24:46.200 --> 24:48.589
Why don't you show Uncle Dave
where we pump the poo out?

24:48.720 --> 24:49.869
Yay, poo pump!

24:57.520 --> 24:59.078
She's great.

25:00.000 --> 25:01.433
I just...

25:01.560 --> 25:04.632
I shouldn't be meeting her at Lego.

25:05.760 --> 25:11.357
I missed out on rattles and potties,
Hungry Caterpillars.

25:12.200 --> 25:15.237
Look, before we do this,
I have to know how you found us.

25:15.360 --> 25:18.318
It's really important,
for Frankie's sake.

25:19.480 --> 25:24.349
A nun and a priest helped you in Poland.
Frankie gave them this.

25:24.480 --> 25:28.393
- She wrote your town on it.
- But how did you get it?

25:29.280 --> 25:33.717
Funny story.
It turns out the priest is my dad.

25:35.240 --> 25:37.993
See, here's what confuses me.

25:39.520 --> 25:42.557
Our wedding. It's you and me.

25:43.520 --> 25:45.397
And then there's this.

25:45.520 --> 25:48.159
And this is you...

25:49.440 --> 25:51.590
with him.

25:52.960 --> 25:54.757
Oh God, you know about Ariel?

25:57.440 --> 26:01.672
OK, um... I know this looks bad but...

26:04.320 --> 26:07.437
Actually, there is no but.
It's just bad.

26:07.560 --> 26:10.074
Can we not do this here?

26:10.200 --> 26:13.397
It's just you get a bit shouty
and high pitched when you're upset

26:13.520 --> 26:14.953
and I don't want Frankie to hear.

26:15.080 --> 26:18.072
- Please.
- I...

26:18.200 --> 26:19.599
- Ow!
- LAYLA: Frankie.

26:19.720 --> 26:21.756
Me and Daddy are just
going for a little walk, OK?

26:21.880 --> 26:24.314
- Uncle Dave will look after you.
- How long are you gonna be?

26:24.440 --> 26:27.034
It's just that when she hits me
with the giraffe, it really hurts.

26:27.160 --> 26:28.718
Yeah, let's play giraffe slaps!

26:28.840 --> 26:30.159
- (GIRAFFE SQUEAKS)
- We could...

26:31.840 --> 26:35.389
How far are we going?
How shouty am I gonna get?

26:35.520 --> 26:39.991
Um... Let's just go
another couple of miles, shall we?

26:40.120 --> 26:42.839
In the interest of full disclosure,
I think I should tell you

26:42.960 --> 26:45.520
that we are from the Vatican.

26:45.640 --> 26:48.279
- I'm a priest. And Celine is a nun.
- (RUTH LAUGHS)

26:48.400 --> 26:51.597
Right!
Got fed up with celibacy, did you?

26:51.720 --> 26:54.473
Can't blame you. Very unhealthy.

26:54.600 --> 26:57.239
No, no,
we actually came to investigate you.

26:57.360 --> 26:58.793
(BOTH LAUGH)

26:58.920 --> 27:02.390
- Of course you did, dear!
- No. Absolutely that's why we're here.

27:02.520 --> 27:04.795
Oh, come on. Be honest with yourselves.

27:04.920 --> 27:08.595
The way you two look at each other?
Hoo-hoo-hoo!

27:08.720 --> 27:11.188
I can see it.

27:11.320 --> 27:14.869
The levels have opened you up.

27:16.240 --> 27:18.515
You're ready for love, honey.

27:19.920 --> 27:23.071
Now I expect you two want to start
with each other but don't be shy now.

27:23.200 --> 27:26.636
It's more of a buffet than a set menu.

27:26.760 --> 27:29.035
(# <i>THE HUNTER</i> BY SLAVES)

27:31.720 --> 27:35.633
# <i>The people are freezing</i>
<i>and the water is warm</i>

27:35.760 --> 27:37.557
# <i>And the ice caps are melting</i>

27:37.680 --> 27:39.750
# <i>What will happen when they're gone?</i>

27:39.880 --> 27:42.189
# <i>Will the experts look stupid</i>

27:42.320 --> 27:44.311
- # <i>And invert the facts</i>
- (MOANING AND GASPING)

27:53.480 --> 27:55.152
You know how to drive
one of these things?

27:55.280 --> 27:58.158
- Ah, not really.
- (ENGINE STARTS)

27:58.280 --> 28:01.477
- But... I am Italian.
- Right.

28:01.600 --> 28:02.715
(LAUGHS)

28:02.840 --> 28:05.274
- JUDE: Whoo!
- (CELINE LAUGHS)

28:16.160 --> 28:18.674
I've been calling! Why the hell
aren't you answering the phone?

28:18.800 --> 28:21.360
- MAN: We're a little busy.
- The DST.

28:21.480 --> 28:23.311
We need to check
the daylight savings time.

28:23.440 --> 28:25.396
- We did, like, 12 times already.
- No, no, no.

28:25.520 --> 28:29.957
We have daylight savings time
but the Russians... The Russians don't.

28:30.080 --> 28:31.559
Guys, guys!

28:31.680 --> 28:35.468
Your president, he doesn't like the gays
and he doesn't like daylight savings.

28:35.600 --> 28:40.151
He got rid of it last year. Yes?
Correct? Yes? Yes! Thank you. Yes. OK?

28:40.280 --> 28:42.430
So I'm sure
that we've taken it into account

28:42.560 --> 28:46.678
but can we please just check it,
the way that their code speaks to ours?

28:46.800 --> 28:50.998
Because otherwise the secondary engine
ignition will be about an hour late,

28:51.120 --> 28:53.873
or an hour early, whatever
the fuck daylight savings time is.

28:54.000 --> 28:56.116
- Scotty, where have you been?
- No! Not now. I'm busy.

28:58.920 --> 29:00.319
There, right there!

29:00.440 --> 29:02.192
Shit, you were right.

29:02.320 --> 29:06.279
OK, people,
we need to rewrite this interface now!

29:06.400 --> 29:08.038
(ALL TALKAT ONCE)

29:18.440 --> 29:22.672
OK, so the boat is the Earth
and I'm that naughty comet, alright?

29:22.800 --> 29:25.837
- Yeah, and I'm Operation Saviour.
- Oh, really?

29:25.960 --> 29:27.791
Well, I bet you can't save the world.

29:28.040 --> 29:29.029
(BLOWS AIR)

29:31.040 --> 29:34.191
Yes, my real name was Hawkwind.

29:35.400 --> 29:37.277
I grew up on the commune with Ariel.

29:37.400 --> 29:38.879
I hated it

29:39.000 --> 29:41.389
so I ran away with him
as soon as I could.

29:41.520 --> 29:43.317
And...

29:44.320 --> 29:47.630
stupidly married him.

29:47.760 --> 29:49.751
I was only 18.

29:50.960 --> 29:53.554
I thought I was in love
but I was young and Ionely

29:53.680 --> 29:56.069
and I wanted to belong somewhere.

29:56.200 --> 29:59.397
- If you're looking for sympathy...
- No, I'm not.

29:59.520 --> 30:02.432
I'm not.
I'm just trying to help you understand

30:02.560 --> 30:04.835
how I could have fucked up
so spectacularly.

30:07.200 --> 30:10.510
Ariel had a real chip on his shoulder
about you

30:10.640 --> 30:13.757
cos your mum was always going on
about how special you were

30:13.880 --> 30:16.235
and it made him feel like shit so...

30:17.560 --> 30:21.314
So... he invented a computer game...

30:22.320 --> 30:24.038
called Doofus.

30:24.160 --> 30:26.116
You were the main character in it.

30:27.600 --> 30:29.033
I don't understand.

30:29.160 --> 30:31.151
He hacked everything
without you realizing.

30:31.280 --> 30:33.635
Your whole life,
so credit records, emails,

30:33.760 --> 30:36.149
he fiddled with everything
to mess it up.

30:36.280 --> 30:37.599
Like what?

30:40.960 --> 30:43.952
Like screwing with your exam results?

30:45.880 --> 30:48.474
So you could have gone to university.

30:48.600 --> 30:51.160
Those rejection letters were all Ariel.

30:54.560 --> 30:56.278
And you knew?

31:01.240 --> 31:03.037
I was young and stupid,

31:03.160 --> 31:06.311
and I never thought of you
as a real person with feelings.

31:06.440 --> 31:08.112
(SNIFFS)

31:09.680 --> 31:13.673
And then one day, we were talking about
how you'd never had a girlfriend.

31:17.080 --> 31:19.674
So you invented one for me?

31:19.800 --> 31:22.758
Yeah. Layla.

31:24.440 --> 31:27.159
We set up a meet cute.

31:27.280 --> 31:29.236
I got in the lift with you
and Ariel hacked it,

31:29.360 --> 31:30.713
made it break down for a few hours.

31:30.840 --> 31:35.118
But when I met you, you were so lovely

31:35.240 --> 31:39.358
and the joke wasn't funny anymore
because everything about you...

31:40.840 --> 31:43.115
was so genuine.

31:44.880 --> 31:49.112
And being Layla
felt so much better than being Hawkwind.

31:50.160 --> 31:54.199
So I split up with Ariel
and I fooled myself.

31:55.080 --> 31:57.514
I thought Doofus was over
and I thought I could just be with you

31:57.640 --> 32:00.438
and be happy and just be Layla.

32:05.640 --> 32:07.232
And then?

32:09.800 --> 32:12.519
And then he showed up on our honeymoon.

32:14.200 --> 32:18.990
Said he'd been biding his time but
that sooner or later we'd be punished.

32:19.120 --> 32:23.193
And he was scary.
Like, eyes bulgy, proper psycho.

32:23.320 --> 32:26.312
And to add to everything,
I'd just found out I was pregnant.

32:27.560 --> 32:29.391
And I panicked.

32:32.800 --> 32:37.476
I... I thought if I just disappeared...

32:38.720 --> 32:41.871
<i>I could protect the baby from him</i>
<i>and protect you.</i>

32:43.200 --> 32:45.714
Everything was a lie.

32:45.840 --> 32:49.389
No. No, everything started as a lie

32:49.520 --> 32:51.590
but we turned into something real.

32:53.760 --> 32:55.318
<i>Cos I did love you, Jamie.</i>

32:56.320 --> 32:59.949
And when we said our wedding vows,
I meant every word.

33:00.080 --> 33:02.389
You were the best thing
that ever happened to me.

33:06.480 --> 33:08.357
Funny, cos you were the worst.

33:10.320 --> 33:12.675
I want details.

33:12.800 --> 33:16.839
And I don't care if it takes all night,
you are gonna tell me everything.

33:21.800 --> 33:23.597
(FRANKIE LAUGHS)

33:28.120 --> 33:29.599
(FRANKIE LAUGHS)

33:32.600 --> 33:34.477
MAN: <i>T minus one minute.</i>

33:38.200 --> 33:41.317
MAN: <i>Fuel. Umbilical purge to open.</i>

33:43.480 --> 33:48.156
Hey! Hey, Scotty, everyone's looking
for you. You were right!

33:48.280 --> 33:51.989
What you did...
You gave us a chance, Scotty.

33:54.520 --> 33:58.354
Well, come on! It's about to launch
and you are the hero of the hours!

33:59.640 --> 34:00.914
Hey.

34:03.200 --> 34:04.553
What is it?

34:06.000 --> 34:08.878
I had to sell out my own sister. (CRIES)

34:09.000 --> 34:13.039
MAN: <i>Umbilical release, primed.</i>
<i>Pressure levels OK.</i>

34:15.120 --> 34:16.348
(CRIES)

34:18.120 --> 34:21.829
MAN: <i>T minus ten, nine...</i>

34:24.840 --> 34:28.355
<i>Six, five, four,</i>

34:29.400 --> 34:33.837
<i>three, two, one.</i>

34:33.960 --> 34:36.474
<i>Trajectory is good. Thrust is good.</i>

34:36.600 --> 34:41.196
<i>Saviour is in the air.</i>
<i>Repeat, Saviour is in the air.</i>

34:43.400 --> 34:44.799
(CELINE LAUGHS)

34:46.480 --> 34:49.710
- Jude, you hold on so tight!
- Because you're a terrible driver!

34:49.840 --> 34:52.353
- (PEOPLE CHEERING)
- It's the Saviour launch.

34:52.480 --> 34:55.119
- I forgot all about it.
- (CHEERING)

34:58.360 --> 35:01.511
We missed it.
Looks like we're camping out tonight.

35:03.120 --> 35:04.712
What?

35:09.920 --> 35:11.512
I know this is going to sound crazy.

35:11.640 --> 35:14.791
Do you remember in Poland,
your granddaughter?

35:15.920 --> 35:19.674
She told me one day
I was going to see four horses.

35:19.800 --> 35:23.031
Awhite, a black, a red and a pale.

35:25.120 --> 35:26.269
Look, it's a sign!

35:29.240 --> 35:31.196
JUDE: It is a sign.

35:33.560 --> 35:35.152
It's a billboard.

35:37.160 --> 35:41.517
Celine, do you really think
the Lord would be communicating to us

35:41.640 --> 35:43.710
using the medium of...

35:45.560 --> 35:47.755
- outside advertising?
- Well, why not?

35:47.880 --> 35:51.190
What if it is a sign,
giving us his blessing?

35:51.320 --> 35:53.390
- For what?
- For the wedding.

35:56.040 --> 35:57.393
That wasn't real.

35:58.680 --> 36:00.671
You kissed me, Jude.

36:01.440 --> 36:04.716
It was not acting. It wasn't.

36:06.600 --> 36:08.670
Was it?

36:32.640 --> 36:34.437
I wasn't acting.

36:36.040 --> 36:39.271
I think about you all the time.

36:39.400 --> 36:43.313
But, Celine,
I've been a priest for 20 years.

36:44.400 --> 36:46.356
I've never broken my vows.

36:46.480 --> 36:48.914
And I don't think you should either.

36:49.840 --> 36:52.354
What if God wants us to?

36:52.480 --> 36:55.233
What if that is a sign?

36:55.360 --> 36:58.158
I'm afraid
it's probably wishful thinking.

36:58.280 --> 36:59.838
Why don't you ask him?

37:00.600 --> 37:01.999
Right now?

37:08.280 --> 37:09.998
Dear Lord.

37:12.280 --> 37:15.113
Dear Lord, I know you have
a lot on your plate right now

37:15.240 --> 37:19.518
but if this is what you want,
please show me a sign.

37:19.640 --> 37:22.393
- (FIREWORKS EXPLODE)
- (CHEERING)

37:31.120 --> 37:33.429
OK, my logical mind

37:33.560 --> 37:37.758
says that that probably has something to
do with the Saviour launch celebration.

37:37.880 --> 37:39.836
Yes, maybe.

37:40.880 --> 37:43.758
But maybe it's God.

37:43.880 --> 37:46.314
What do you want it to be, Jude?

37:53.440 --> 37:54.839
(FIREWORKS EXPLODE)

38:07.400 --> 38:08.992
Told you we'd meet again.

38:11.040 --> 38:12.996
My husband is dying.

38:13.120 --> 38:18.069
Couldn't have given me
one minute with him? One?

38:18.200 --> 38:20.555
- McNeil, you're coming with us.
- What the hell's going on?

38:20.680 --> 38:22.193
Whoa, what?

38:22.320 --> 38:24.595
Marine Corps Intelligence.
We have orders to debrief her.

38:24.720 --> 38:26.153
I arrested her. She is my prisoner!

38:26.280 --> 38:28.589
She'll be returned to you
once the interview is complete.

38:42.080 --> 38:44.992
Hey. I want you to see this.

38:45.120 --> 38:46.712
I don't care about the launch.

38:46.840 --> 38:49.434
Just trust me, OK?

38:52.000 --> 38:53.638
This is streaming live.

39:00.920 --> 39:02.638
(DOOR OPENS)

39:03.960 --> 39:06.190
I couldn't change the outcome

39:06.320 --> 39:09.551
but I did make sure
they got a chance to say goodbye.

39:39.000 --> 39:41.594
So, what do we do now?

39:42.560 --> 39:44.391
I don't know.

39:44.520 --> 39:47.876
Try not to argue in front of Frankie,
I suppose.

39:49.920 --> 39:52.309
I guess I should demand
alternate weekends with her

39:52.440 --> 39:55.477
but there's only one more of those
before the apocalypse.

40:00.800 --> 40:02.552
Seven years.

40:02.680 --> 40:06.559
All it would have taken was one message,
just to put me out of my misery.

40:06.680 --> 40:11.151
No. No, I told you,
I couldn't risk Ariel finding us.

40:11.280 --> 40:13.555
Please, Jamie, we've been up all night.

40:13.680 --> 40:15.955
Let's just get some sleep
before we do more, OK?

40:16.080 --> 40:20.198
Why were you with him
in Moscow a few weeks ago?

40:23.040 --> 40:26.350
I saw there was a reward out on him.

40:26.480 --> 40:28.994
I was sick of never having any money
for Frankie

40:29.120 --> 40:32.715
so I called the police and they set up
a trap for him with me as the bait

40:32.840 --> 40:34.796
only it all went to sh... shit!

40:39.000 --> 40:40.069
Frankie!

40:40.840 --> 40:42.671
Mate, can you hear me?

40:44.120 --> 40:46.350
She's gone! Frankie's gone!

40:48.160 --> 40:50.754
Mate... No, no, it's OK. What happened?

40:52.200 --> 40:53.918
Your brother.

40:59.960 --> 41:03.111
Good news, Grandma.
I've got your little donor.

41:03.240 --> 41:05.310
All five pints of her.

41:05.440 --> 41:07.874
SUTTON: <i>Wonderful. Bring her here.</i>

41:08.000 --> 41:10.389
Yeah, you know what?
I'm not gonna do that.

41:10.520 --> 41:13.557
I'm keeping her as an insurance policy.

41:14.560 --> 41:17.279
Oh, and by the way, I had to get rid
of your little Irish lapdog.

41:17.400 --> 41:19.914
<i>- What have you done to her?</i>
- She'll live.

41:20.040 --> 41:23.112
Which is more than I would have, right?

41:23.240 --> 41:25.515
<i>I don't know what you mean.</i>

41:25.640 --> 41:27.870
Yes, you do, Grandma.

41:28.000 --> 41:31.470
You were going to get rid of me
the moment I got you the girl.

41:31.600 --> 41:35.309
Well, sorry to disappoint you
but we're doing things my way now.

41:35.960 --> 41:38.155
You don't get the girl
until the very last minute

41:38.280 --> 41:41.670
when I'm safely inside the bunker.
Am I clear?

41:41.800 --> 41:43.358
<i>Perfectly.</i>

41:43.480 --> 41:46.517
Good! Oh, and one other thing...

41:46.640 --> 41:48.278
I'm gonna need a plus one in the bunker.

41:48.400 --> 41:50.197
The wife's coming too.

41:52.080 --> 41:54.310
<i>That</i> is how you negotiate.

41:55.120 --> 41:57.190
Pretty impressive, huh?

41:58.240 --> 42:00.549
Hey, don't look so scared.

42:00.680 --> 42:03.558
I'm just like your dad, only cooler.

42:08.960 --> 42:12.873
Me, you and your mum
are gonna be a family.

42:14.280 --> 42:18.034
<i>We're gonna be together</i>
<i>for the rest of our lives.</i>

42:18.920 --> 42:20.797
<i>Everything's gonna be fine.</i>

42:21.640 --> 42:24.791
<i>We're gonna be happy... forever.</i>

